     "verify": "// paste under b7-01's varint/key/hex helpers:\nfunc lenField(_ f: UInt64, _ s: String) -> [UInt8] { key(f, 2) + varint(UInt64(s.utf8.count)) + Array(s.utf8) }\n// 1. old decoder (knows only field 1) walks a message with new fields 3 + 4:\n//    executed → id=300, unknown fields skipped=2, no error\n// 2. v1 bytes with name at field 2, decoder expecting field 7:\n//    executed → name stays \"\" — silent loss\nfunc zigzagDecode(_ n: UInt64) -> Int64 { Int64(n >> 1) ^ -Int64(n & 1) }\nprint(zigzagDecode(1))          // -1 — int32-encoded 1 misread by a sint32 decoder (executed)\nprint(varint(15 << 3 | 0))      // [120]    — fields 1–15: one-byte key (executed)\nprint(varint(16 << 3 | 0))      // [128, 1] — field 16+: two bytes (executed)\n// count:0 vs absent — both serialize to zero bytes (executed, b7-01's omission rule)\n// UNRECOGNIZED enums + unknownFields re-serialization: documented SwiftProtobuf behavior",
