      "definition": "You never run ONE version of your app — review latency, phased release, and user inertia mean a FLEET of versions is live for months, all talking to today's backend. Update strategy is managing that fleet: a server-driven version gate (minimum version → blocking update screen; current version → dismissible nudge), compared NUMERICALLY — never as strings — failing OPEN when the config is unreachable, with protocol compatibility (b7-02's discipline) as the real safety net underneath, because no gate can force an update instantly.",
